com.mojang.serialization

Class KeyCompressor<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mojang.serialization.KeyCompressor<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the serialized form.

    public final class KeyCompressor<T>
extends Object
    An immutable collection of indexed, string-convertible keys. When serializing and deserializing maps with compressed keys, a key compressor is used to associate an integer index with each possible key.
    Implementation Note:
    The implementation uses two hash tables to associate contiguous indices with keys in order to ensure both compression and decompression run in constant time. Using a single array of T[this.size()] is more straightforward, but incurs linear run time for compression.
    See Also:
    DynamicOps.compressMaps()

    • Constructor Detail

      • KeyCompressor

        public KeyCompressor(DynamicOps<T> ops,
                     Stream<T> keyStream)
        Constructs a new key compressor for the given key stream. If a key appears in the key stream more than once, the second and subsequent appearances are ignored.

        The key stream is consumed in the constructor. It should be finite, or else this constructor will run forever.

        Parameters:
        ops - The DynamicOps instance defining the serialized form.
        keyStream - A stream of keys this key compressor compresses.

    • Method Detail

      • decompress

        public T decompress(int key)
        Returns the key associated with the given key index, or null if the key index does not correspond to a key.

        Caution: This is one of the few methods in DFU that may return null.

        Implementation Note:
        This method incurs one lookup and runs in constant time.
        Parameters:
        key - The key index.
        Returns:
        The key associated with the key index, or null if the key index is invalid.

      • compress

        public int compress(String key)
        Returns the key index associated with the key the given string represents. If the argument does not represent a valid key, -1 is returned.
        Implementation Note:
        This method incurs at most two lookups and runs in constant time.
        Parameters:
        key - The string representation of a key.
        Returns:
        The index associated with that key, or null if the key does not exist.
        See Also:
        compress(Object)
